Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Virginia Military Institute (VMI) in which he expressed gratitude to the men and women of the armed forces and veterans. He highlighted the importance of honor and service, and praised the tradition and legacy of VMI in producing educated and capable leaders. Pence also emphasized the Trump administration's commitment to rebuilding and strengthening the military, as well as its efforts to promote peace through strength. He encouraged the cadets to approach their calling with humility, embrace orientation to authority, and practice self-control and discipline. Pence concluded by urging the cadets to be men and women of integrity and to build lives that will serve the nation for generations to come.